Jamie Yuccas, thank you.

00:13:16.29 --> 00:13:18.63
From the snow and ice of the Olympics

00:13:18.63 --> 00:13:20.64
to the gridiron of the Super Bowl,

00:13:20.64 --> 00:13:23.28
the big game is just days away and the final preparations

00:13:23.28 --> 00:13:26.10
are being put in place for the teams, the halftime

00:13:26.10 --> 00:13:29.56
show and the high profile commercials.

00:13:29.56 --> 00:13:33.47
CBS's Carter Evans reports from Los Angeles.

00:13:33.47 --> 00:13:35.42
Just before kickoff on Super Bowl

00:13:35.42 --> 00:13:40.28
Sunday, the skies above so far will come along.

00:13:40.28 --> 00:13:43.13
America's fastest fighter jets will do a flyover

00:13:43.13 --> 00:13:46.61
during the National Anthem to honor the US Air Force.

00:13:46.61 --> 00:13:50.81
And we got a preview from inside the cockpit.

00:13:50.81 --> 00:13:52.55
That takeoff is just so powerful.

00:13:52.55 --> 00:13:55.88
On the ground, emotions are sky high from both the Rams

00:13:55.88 --> 00:13:56.97
and the Bengals.

00:13:56.97 --> 00:13:58.19
This is an exciting moment.

00:13:58.19 --> 00:13:59.48
Everybody thinks about it forever.

00:13:59.48 --> 00:14:00.92
There's a lot of good positive juice.

00:14:00.92 --> 00:14:02.55
I mean, everybody's excited about this.

00:14:02.55 --> 00:14:04.15
But it's not just a game.

00:14:04.15 --> 00:14:06.12
Lays.

00:14:06.12 --> 00:14:07.08
Do you have barbecue?

00:14:07.08 --> 00:14:08.94
Or cheddar jalapeno?

00:14:08.94 --> 00:14:11.34
This year, a 30-second commercial during the game

00:14:11.34 --> 00:14:14.49
sells for a record $7 million.

00:14:14.49 --> 00:14:17.64
You can expect the return of the Clydesdales, a Super Bowl

00:14:17.64 --> 00:14:20.01
staple.

00:14:20.01 --> 00:14:23.40
For the first time ever, the halftime show is all hip-hop.

00:14:23.40 --> 00:14:26.94
We're going to open more doors for hip-hop artists

00:14:26.94 --> 00:14:27.75
in the future.

00:14:27.75 --> 00:14:29.73
But a new controversy as Snoop Dogg

00:14:29.73 --> 00:14:32.67
was sued this week by a woman who claims he sexually

00:14:32.67 --> 00:14:35.37
assaulted her in 2013.

00:14:35.37 --> 00:14:39.12
Snoop Dogg has not responded directly to the lawsuit.

00:14:39.12 --> 00:14:41.16
All the excitement inside the stadium

00:14:41.16 --> 00:14:44.40
may have to wait for the more than 70,000 fans who

00:14:44.40 --> 00:14:47.60
first have to prove they're vaccinated or COVID negative.

00:14:47.60 --> 00:14:49.14
We're following the county guidelines

00:14:49.14 --> 00:14:52.62
which are two-shot vaccination or negative tests.

00:14:52.62 --> 00:14:55.86
We will have some testing available on site, though.

00:14:55.86 --> 00:14:58.14
As a last resort before you turn someone away?

00:14:58.14 --> 00:14:59.70
That is the last resort, correct.

00:14:59.70 --> 00:15:02.97
Now, as out-of-town fans begin to arrive here in LA,

00:15:02.97 --> 00:15:06.00
they may be shocked at how hot it is here.

00:15:06.00 --> 00:15:09.27
We are under a winter heat advisory right now.

00:15:09.27 --> 00:15:12.81
Temperatures could be close to 90 degrees by kickoff.

00:15:12.81 --> 00:15:16.60
If that happens, it would set a record for the Super Bowl.

00:15:16.60 --> 00:15:17.46
Norah.

00:15:17.46 --> 00:15:18.36
That is hot.

00:15:18.36 --> 00:15:19.93
Carter Evans, thank you.

00:15:19.93 --> 00:15:22.17
Well, still ahead on tonight's CBS Evening News,

00:15:22.17 --> 00:15:24.12
a deadly standoff in Phoenix.

00:15:24.12 --> 00:15:28.08
Nine police officers hit in a barrage of gunfire.

00:15:28.08 --> 00:15:31.29
And the new space telescope posted its first selfie

00:15:31.29 --> 00:15:33.26
a million miles from home.

00:15:33.26 --> 00:15:38.33


00:15:38.33 --> 00:15:41.96
Nine police officers in Phoenix were hit in a hail of bullets

00:15:41.96 --> 00:15:43.91
when a gunman ambushed them today.

00:15:43.91 --> 00:15:46.64
Five officers were shot and four wounded

00:15:46.64 --> 00:15:49.16
by shrapnel or ricocheting bullets.

00:15:49.16 --> 00:15:50.80
All are expected to survive.

00:15:50.80 --> 00:15:52.55
Police ordered another person in the house

00:15:52.55 --> 00:15:54.65
to bring out a baby who was inside.

00:15:54.65 --> 00:15:56.84
Police later found the gunman dead and injured woman

00:15:56.84 --> 00:15:58.47
later died at the hospital.

00:15:58.47 --> 00:16:00.15
The baby was not hurt.

00:16:00.15 --> 00:16:02.27
And tonight, a look at the first selfie

00:16:02.27 --> 00:16:04.73
shot by the James Webb Space Telescope.

00:16:04.73 --> 00:16:08.30
It shows the Observatory's 21-foot wide primary mirror

00:16:08.30 --> 00:16:10.85
as it orbits the sun a million miles from Earth.

00:16:10.85 --> 00:16:13.64
Another image shows a mosaic of multiple blurry images

00:16:13.64 --> 00:16:16.38
of a star which may not look like much now,

00:16:16.38 --> 00:16:20.12
but that star is being used to align the 18 segments that make

00:16:20.12 --> 00:16:22.91
up the telescope's main mirror.

00:16:22.91 --> 00:16:23.42
All right.

00:16:23.42 --> 00:16:26.00
On the Road is next with the musical tradition

00:16:26.00 --> 00:16:30.86
you have to hear and see to believe.

00:16:30.86 --> 00:16:33.96
If you can't watch the CBS Evening News, you can listen.

00:16:33.96 --> 00:16:35.96
Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts.

00:16:35.96 --> 00:16:36.86
Sponsored by Crest.

00:16:36.86 --> 00:16:40.80


00:16:40.80 --> 00:16:43.35
For this week's On The Road, CBS's Steve Hartman

00:16:43.35 --> 00:16:47.34
checks into a hotel with quite the view but even better

00:16:47.34 --> 00:16:48.04
acoustics.

00:16:48.04 --> 00:16:51.87


00:16:51.87 --> 00:16:55.11
Every year, 600 of the best high school singers

00:16:55.11 --> 00:16:58.56
from across Kentucky gather to practice and perform

00:16:58.56 --> 00:17:00.96
in Louisville's Convention Center.

00:17:00.96 --> 00:17:05.01
And all these booming voices have to stay somewhere.

00:17:05.01 --> 00:17:06.66
It can get a little noisy.

00:17:06.66 --> 00:17:11.25
For that reason, the Hyatt Regency offers earplugs,

00:17:11.25 --> 00:17:15.78
knowing a gross violation of the quiet hours is not only likely,

00:17:15.78 --> 00:17:18.75
it's a 35-year tradition.

00:17:18.75 --> 00:17:22.62
Back in 1987, late one night, a small group

00:17:22.62 --> 00:17:25.35
of kids still wired from practice

00:17:25.35 --> 00:17:27.55
gathered along the balcony here.

00:17:27.55 --> 00:17:30.96
Everybody's chatting away, waving hi to each other.

00:17:30.96 --> 00:17:34.35
Choir Director Brett Burton was a student at the time.

00:17:34.35 --> 00:17:37.50
There's just certain things that happen in the life that

00:17:37.50 --> 00:17:38.85
leave a memory on you.

00:17:38.85 --> 00:17:40.83
And this is one of them?

00:17:40.83 --> 00:17:42.66
It was just something amazing.

00:17:42.66 --> 00:17:47.10
Today, the same wonder unfolds in much the same way.

00:17:47.10 --> 00:17:54.66
The waving, the ruckus, and then out of nowhere, the hum.

00:17:54.66 --> 00:17:56.24
Someone sings a pitch.

00:17:56.24 --> 00:17:58.34
It can be anyone from anywhere.

00:17:58.34 --> 00:18:01.23
Once one person starts, everyone wants to be a part of it.

00:18:01.23 --> 00:18:03.21
And eventually, the entire hotel catches on.

00:18:03.21 --> 00:18:05.05
And then you're singing the National Anthem.

00:18:05.05 --> 00:18:17.16


00:18:17.16 --> 00:18:19.77
Some say it's the acoustics.

00:18:19.77 --> 00:18:22.32
Others the sheer volume of talent.

00:18:22.32 --> 00:18:24.39
But whatever the reason, one thing

00:18:24.39 --> 00:18:31.08
is clear, whoever opted for the earplugs made a grave mistake.

00:18:31.08 --> 00:18:32.49
It's like a cylinder of sound.

00:18:32.49 --> 00:18:33.97
It's all around you.

00:18:33.97 --> 00:18:34.81
So surreal.

00:18:34.81 --> 00:18:35.31
It's--

00:18:35.31 --> 00:18:38.14


00:18:38.14 --> 00:18:40.72
And it's completely organic.

00:18:40.72 --> 00:18:43.12
There's no planning or adult direction.

00:18:43.12 --> 00:18:46.42
This is all kids from all walks of life

00:18:46.42 --> 00:18:48.40
who every year make it a priority

00:18:48.40 --> 00:18:55.37
to fill this hotel atrium with a riveting reminder

00:18:55.37 --> 00:18:58.91
that we are not a nation of soloists,

00:18:58.91 --> 00:19:02.63
but a chorus of shared values that when

00:19:02.63 --> 00:19:06.95
joined together resonate like nothing

00:19:06.95 --> 00:19:08.38
the world has ever heard.

00:19:08.38 --> 00:19:12.50


00:19:12.50 --> 00:19:16.08
Steve Hartman On The Road in Louisville, Kentucky.

00:19:16.08 --> 00:19:21.24


00:19:21.24 --> 00:19:23.76
I don't know about you, but I needed that tonight.

